window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b><i>Dragons were never meant to be simple circus attractions.</i></b><br> <br> The Dragon Shifter among the men of the Chinese Zodiac had disappeared without a trace, up until a meddling Rooster Shifter dug up his whereabouts. And <b><i>Jun Shen</i></b>, the snake shifter, enforcer of magical tenants, and Advanced Math professor within Graves Academy is obligated to look into the matter. When he meets a man more broken than even the Rabbit Shifter who he... still hasn't entirely gotten over, he finds himself conflicted on where he stands in this realm of fated mates and damaged men.<br> <br> With a limiter collar suppressing his power, <b><i>Jarek Milan</i></b> is a prisoner of Avro's dark and magical circus. Through countless escape attempts, the light at the end of the tunnel only seems to grow more distant. But when the circus pitches its tent at Graves Academy, he may finally have the help he needs, in so very many ways.<br> <br> Set in the same Universe as The Zodiac Werewolf, this is the second book in the Shifters of the Chinese Zodiac MM+ Paranormal Romance Series. Listeners who love dark carnivals, healing through k!nk, dominant and sinister men who have a soft spot for their mates, and the occasional magical cupcake will love the twisted tale of the Zodiac Shifters of Graves Academy.</p> <p><b>While there are many moments of fun and spice, this is still a DARK work of fiction. Please check the authors website for CWs</b></p>"; 
